The paper focuses on learning social media content representation by fusing textual, acoustic, and visual features. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), multimedia (cs.MM), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), and computer vision (cs.CV).
